	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64696016">Why do people always forget the most important aspect? Mars has only one third of the gravity Earth has. And that means that no one should live for any longer time period on Mars, lest they can't return to Earth anymore due to muscle and bone atrophies. And this makes any human Mars mission extremely expensive, as you have to return everyone to Earth within one or two years.
<p>
Until we know how we can create artificial gravity for a whole habitat on Mars, we should not even start to create a permanent one.</p></div>
	</div>

